  -
    type: table
    tab: Virtual column
    caption: This example creates a virtual column using a <code>template</code> that refers to existing columns in the CSV. The result is a column named <code>Source</code> where the value is a link to <code>Source→Link</code> using the <code>Source→Name</code> column.
    config:
      file: /data/example/gapmap.csv
      columns:
        - name: "Source"
          template: "<a href=\"{{ Source→Link }}\">{{ Source→Name }}</a>"
        - name: "Ethnic groups availability→Broad groupings (e.g. White, Black, Asian, mixed, other)→Rating"
          rename: "Broad groupings e.g. White, Black, Asian, mixed, other"
          width: "15%"
          align: center
          heatmap: true
          scale:
            stops:
